{
  "texts": [
    "There are five Stokes arrows on five singular directions.",
    "We choose a reference direction b as indicated in Figure 15.",
    "Again, if we choose an appropriate framing (which is indeed given by the Legendre transform), we can assume that the formal monodromy has the form h = 0 τ -1 0 with a conjugcacy class for the formal monodromy corresponding to one value of τ.",
    "The Stokes matrices have (with the numbering of strands as shown in Figure 15) the form S 1 = 1 0 t 1 1, S 2 = 1 t 2 0 1, S 3 = 1 0 t 3 1, S 4 = 1 t 4 0 1, S 5 = 1 0 t 5 1.",
    "Let us denote by Sto i, i = 1,."
  ]
}